Step 1 — Update networking on the capsule

satellite-maintain service stop
Update IP via nmtui to DMZ IP
satellite-maintain service start

Step 2 — Update DNS

Update A record in caal.dev zone to new DMZ IP
Update PTR record to new DMZ IP

Step 3 — Request firewall rules from network team

DMZ hosts → Capsule DMZ IP — port 443
Capsule DMZ IP → Satellite Server — port 443
Capsule DMZ IP → Satellite Server — port 5646

Step 4 — Validate

Verify capsule shows green in Satellite UI
Verify content sync still works
Register a DMZ test host through the capsule

That's it. The FQDN pln-capsule-dmz01.caal.dev never changes — just the IP. So once DNS and firewall are updated everything should come back up cleanly.
